ğŸ”¹ Equivalent Definitions of Tree (VERY IMPORTANT)

For a graph with n vertices, the following are equivalent:

Connected and acyclic

Connected with nâˆ’1 edges

Acyclic with nâˆ’1 edges

Exactly one simple path between every pair of vertices

ğŸ“Œ GATE Trap:
Questions often ask which condition is sufficient.

ğŸ”¹ Rooted Tree

A rooted tree has:

One designated node called root

Direction away from the root (implicit)

Terms:

Parent

Child

Leaf (external node) â†’ no children

Internal node â†’ at least one child

Level / Height / Depth

ğŸ”¹ Degree in Trees

Degree of a node = number of children

Degree of tree = maximum degree of any node

ğŸ”¹ Binary Tree (HIGH WEIGHTAGE)

A binary tree is a rooted tree where:

Each node has at most 2 children

Left child & Right child are distinguished

ğŸ”¹ Types of Binary Trees
1ï¸âƒ£ Full Binary Tree

Every node has 0 or 2 children

2ï¸âƒ£ Complete Binary Tree

All levels filled except possibly last

Last level filled from left to right

ğŸ“Œ Used heavily in Heaps

3ï¸âƒ£ Perfect Binary Tree

All internal nodes have 2 children

All leaves at same level

